Rama the elephant was euthanized this week at the age of 31 . 
  His leg was injured after female elephants shoved him into a moat in 1990 . 
  Rama completed paintings with his trunk and reportedly earned over $100,000 in sales . 
  Oregon Zoo officials said he had 'sharp decline in mobility' and 'the most humane course of action was to euthanize him' Animal rights activists have said he was placed with female elephants at a young age . 
 